OL,3,CNew rule approved to crack down on
OL,4,Csecond homes in national park
OL,6,FIn a statement, the park authority
OL,7,Fsaid: "The Eryri National Park
OL,8,FAuthority is the second Planning
OL,9,FAuthority in Wales to implement this
OL,10,Fnew measure, following in the
OL,11,Ffootsteps of Cyngor Gwynedd who has
OL,12,Fimplemented the Article 4 Direction
OL,13,Fsince September 2024 in those areas of
OL,14,FGwynedd that do not fall within the
OL,15,FNational Park boundary.
OL,17,F"The Article 4 Direction will not be
OL,18,Fretrospective and therefore will not
OL,19,Faffect properties in Eryri used as
OL,20,Fsecond homes or short-term holiday
OL,21,Flets before the 1 June 2025."
